@startuml agent-payment-happy-path
title x402 Agent Payment — Happy Path (Standard x402 v1 + EIP-3009 + Self-Hosted Facilitator)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam participantBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam participantBorderColor #2196F3

actor "AI Agent" as Agent
participant "Developer Service\n(withPaywall middleware\n+ inline facilitator)" as Service
participant "PaymentSplitter\nContract (Arc Testnet)" as Splitter
participant "USDC\n(0x3600...0000)" as USDC
participant "Arc Testnet RPC" as Arc

== Step 1: Discover ==
Agent -> Service : GET /api/data\n(no payment)

Service -> Agent : HTTP 402 application/json\nBody: {\n  "x402Version": 1,\n  "accepts": [{\n    "scheme": "exact",\n    "network": "arc-testnet",\n    "maxAmountRequired": "10000",\n    "resource": "...",\n    "payTo": "0xSplitter...",\n    "asset": "0x3600...0000",\n    "extra": {\n      "assetTransferMethod": "eip3009",\n      "name": "USDC",\n      "version": "2"\n    }, ...\n  }]\n}

== Step 2: Agent signs (off-chain, no gas) ==
Agent -> Agent : Build EIP-712 typed-data:\n  domain  = {name:"USDC", version:"2",\n             chainId:5042002,\n             verifyingContract:0x3600...}\n  message = {\n    from: agent,\n    to: splitter,\n    value: 10000,\n    validAfter: 0,\n    validBefore: now+60,\n    nonce: random32bytes\n  }\nSign with agent wallet → 65-byte sig

== Step 3: Retry with X-PAYMENT ==
Agent -> Service : GET /api/data\nX-PAYMENT: base64(JSON({\n  "x402Version": 1,\n  "scheme": "exact",\n  "network": "arc-testnet",\n  "payload": {\n    "signature": "0x...",\n    "authorization": {from,to,value,\n                       validAfter,validBefore,nonce},\n    "developerId": "0xDev..."\n  }\n}))

== Step 4: Off-chain verify (facilitator) ==
Service -> Service : 1. Decode X-PAYMENT\n2. EIP-712 ecrecover\n   (recovered == authorization.from)\n3. Check to == splitterAddress\n4. Check value >= maxAmountRequired\n5. Check validBefore > now + 5s\n6. Check network match\n7. Check NonceStore.has({from,nonce}) == false; insert

== Step 5: On-chain settle (facilitator pays gas in USDC) ==
Service -> Splitter : payWithAuthorization(\n  developerId, value, validAfter,\n  validBefore, nonce, v, r, s\n)\nrelayer signs tx

Splitter -> USDC : transferWithAuthorization(\n  from=agent, to=splitter,\n  value, validAfter,\n  validBefore, nonce, v, r, s\n)
USDC -> USDC : ecrecover, check\nauthorizationState[from][nonce] == false\nset authorizationState[from][nonce] = true\ntransfer USDC: agent → splitter
USDC --> Splitter : ok

Splitter -> Splitter : developers[developerId].balance\n  += value - platformFee\nplatformBalance += platformFee\nemit PaymentReceived(...)

Splitter --> Service : tx hash
Service -> Arc : getTransactionReceipt(tx)
Arc --> Service : status: success

== Step 6: 200 OK with X-PAYMENT-RESPONSE ==
Service -> Agent : HTTP 200 OK\nX-PAYMENT-RESPONSE: base64(JSON({\n  "success": true,\n  "transaction": "0x...",\n  "network": "arc-testnet",\n  "payer": "0xAgent..."\n}))\n\n{ ...resource data... }

== Step 7: Developer withdraws (async) ==
note over Splitter : Developer balance accumulates\nover many payments
"Developer" -> Splitter : withdraw(amount)
Splitter -> USDC : transfer(developer, amount)
USDC -> "Developer" : USDC arrives

@enduml
